-- Itron to Modernize Water-Meter Infrastructure for Spain Utility
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-04-09T14:57:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-09/itron-to-modernize-water-meter-infrastructure-for-spain-utility.html
Itron Inc. (ITRI) , the biggest U.S. maker
of meters that reduce waste and energy use, said a Spanish water
utility serving 3.5 million residents selected the company to
modernize its water-metering infrastructure.  Terms weren’t disclosed by Liberty Lake, Washington-based
Itron in today’s statement for the five-year deal that includes
installing 100,000 water meters with Aguas de Valencia, which
operates mainly in Valencia, Catalonia and northern Spain.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
